# agenticDiagram — optional configuration.
#
# Every variable here is OPTIONAL; the app runs fine with none set. To use them,
# copy this file to `.env` (which is gitignored) and uncomment what you need.
#
# Notes:
#   - Client-exposed vars MUST keep the `MERMAID_` prefix — Vite only forwards
#     that prefix to browser code (see `envPrefix` in vite.config.js).
#   - `MERMAID_BASE_PATH` is read at build time by svelte.config.js; the rest
#     are read via import.meta.env in src/lib/util/env.ts.
#   - This is a standalone, local-first app. It has NO analytics and makes no
#     external network calls. The only optional outbound call is the in-app AI
#     assistant, which talks directly to Google's Gemini API using the API key
#     YOU enter in the UI (stored client-side only — never in the repo/build).
#
# IMPORTANT for a Docker/Cloud Run build: `.env` is excluded by .dockerignore,
# so these are NOT picked up inside the image. To set any of them for a deployed
# build, pass them as Docker build args / Cloud Build substitutions (they are
# baked at build time by Vite), not as Cloud Run runtime env vars.

# --- Deployment ---
# Serve the app under a sub-path instead of the domain root, e.g. "/diagrams".
# Default: "" (served at root).
# MERMAID_BASE_PATH=

# --- Privacy / legal ---
# URL of your privacy policy. When set, the shield icon links straight to it;
# otherwise a built-in "your data stays in your browser" dialog is shown.
# Default: "".
# MERMAID_PRIVACY_POLICY_URL=
# Hide the privacy/security button entirely. Set to "true" to hide.
# Default: false.
# MERMAID_HIDE_PRIVACY_POLICY=
